10 approved food solvents that limit the potency of the product, which contains levels
11 of residual solvents higher than is allowed in the U.S. Pharmacopeia 467, or a single
12 serving size of greater than eighty milligrams.
13 B. For the purposes of this Section, the following terms shall have the
14 following meanings:
15 (1) "Synthesized" means created by chemical synthesis or biosynthetic
16 methods including fermentation, recombitant techniques, yeast derived enzymatic
17 techniques, and oxidation, rather than by traditional food preparation techniques,
18 such as heating or extracting.
19 (2) "Semi-synthetic alkaloid" means a substance derived from an alkaloid
20 occurring in kratom that has been chemically altered through chemical reactions such
